{'id': 2011, 'project': {'name': 'Snapshot', 'description': "Snapshot started as a voting platform designed to allow onchain organizations to vote easily without gas fees. Its strength lies in its flexibility and high customization, catering to the diverse needs of its users. This includes options for calculating users' voting power, selecting different voting mechanisms, and managing proposal and vote validation rules.\n\nAs the gas cost dropped with the maturity of L2s and the need for more decentralized and trustless voting grew, we developed Snapshot X, an onchain voting protocol. Unlike the original Snapshot, Snapshot X operates fully onchain using a set of modular smart contracts. This shift makes Snapshot censorship resistant, with onchain and cross-chain voting power computation and trustless execution, while keeping gas costs to the minimal extent possible.", 'website': 'https://snapshot.box/#/'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': 19867, 'ethAddress': '0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Snapshot', 'description': 'Snapshot', 'website': 'https://snapshot.box/#/'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 8}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 3}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': "As a citizen (Joxes), I'd say it’s pretty obvious that Snapshot is fulfilling its purpose as the canonical tool for vetoing proposals."}]}

{'id': 1828, 'project': {'name': 'Pairwise', 'description': 'Pairwise was designed to make voting to distribute Retro Funding simple and fun. Pairwise is an open-source, off-chain voting dapp (like Snapshot) that streamlines community signaling by letting users select between just two options and then aggregating their choices into a quantifiable result.
Pairwise is designed to be user-friendly and intuitive, allowing users to make many simple choices and then the algorithm behind the scenes pumps out a final ranking for them to adjust or approve. 

* RF3: Served as an alternative tool for creating lists and subcategories of 600+ projects.
* RF4: Ran its own independent experiment involving all stakeholders to signal how to distribute RF promoting project discovery with pseudonymous voting.
* RF5: After great work on RF4, was invited to be a fun voting option to gamify and simplify the badgeholder decision making process. Allowing Badgeholders to create their ballot by comparing projects.', 'website': 'https://www.pairwise.vote/'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': 19867, 'ethAddress': '0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Pairwise', 'description': 'Pairwise', 'website': 'https://www.pairwise.vote/'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 6}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 1}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': "As a citizen (Joxes), this tool helped me during RPGF3 by providing some ordering when I began evaluating projects and applying some pseudo-calculus. {'id': 1865, 'project': {'name': 'Superfluid', 'description': "Superfluid is the leading asset streaming protocol that brings subscriptions, salaries, vesting, and rewards distributions to DAOs and crypto-native businesses worldwide.

The protocol has been live on Optimism since March 2022 and on Base since July 2023. It has been empowering developers with a crypto-native financial primitive, money streaming, and a modular smart contracts framework to build applications that leverage a formula-based balance and gasless, liquid, ongoing value transfer.

To date 31,769 streams have been started on Optimism and 577,985 on Base for a combined total volume of over $170M.

Superfluid is designed to minimize its TVL in favor of making assets available to sender or recipient at all times, minimizing funds locked in smart contracts. As such its impact is better measures in total volume transferred, number of total or active streams, total number of users and daily active users. When measuring the protocol activity it's important to not only rely on the on-chain transaction to smart contracts, but also on the the inner mechanics of the protocol (i.e. by evaluating the actions triggered via callData or by using the protocol subgraph).

On the alignment with Optimism and Retro Funding Round 4
- Superfluid is builder-centric. A developer tool with clear focus on onboarding more developers to build more apps. As such, it’s additive to Optimism’s own goals.
- Superfluid is supporting long term, real world use cases, like Salaries, Subscriptions, Memberships, Rentals, Airdrops, Grants distribution as well as entirely novel applications in DeFi, SocialFi and beyond.

Superfluid Protocol has been used by the Optimism Foundation to stream the RPGF3 grants, and will be used again in the upcoming RPGF4 round, providing the rails for a seamless funds distribution.

The protocol has been designed around builders and developers, with a set of tools available for building, debugging and data retrieval that empower new applications development. Here you can see an overview of projects built on Superfluid that have added value (and usage) to the Optimism and Base networks: https://www.superfluid.finance/post/how-superfluid-protocol-is-empowering-onchain-builders

If you have any questions or would like to learn more about Superfluid, please reach out to mdali.eth on Warpcast or Twitter/X.", 'website': ''}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': '415745', 'ethAddress': '0xd6c09962e907428112069273d5c0dc861e7b1c57'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Superfluid', 'description': 'Superfluid', 'website': ''}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 9}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 3}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': 'Enhances fund distribution in the Optimism ecosystem by streamlining grant management, enabling real-time payments, and offering transparent tracking for recipients. {'id': 2174, 'project': {'name': 'Optimystics Tools', 'description': "A suite of open-source software designed to empower communities with gamified governance and fractal democracy processes on the Superchain.

Optimystics Tools is a suite of open-source software designed to empower communities with innovative governance solutions on the Superchain. Our toolkit, centered around the Respect Game, includes applications for decentralized decision-making, reputation management, and collective action. Since October 2023, we've been developing and refining these tools, which form the technical foundation of Optimism Fractal's weekly events.

Our initial toolset laid the groundwork for fractal democracy experiments, enabling peer-reviewed contribution evaluation and democratic council formation. This has evolved into a comprehensive ecosystem of governance tools, including a comprehensive Respect Games app for gamified governance, Fractalgram app for live community engagement, and ORDAO smart contracts for optimistic, respect-based onchain execution. By providing this infrastructure, we've created a laboratory for governance innovation within the Optimism ecosystem. Our tools have not only supported Optimism Fractal but have also been adopted by other communities, demonstrating their versatility and potential for wider impact in decentralized governance.

This work has not been funded by the Collective outside of the RetroPGF Round 3 grant shown below, which supported the team who started Optimism Fractal as well as our work with several other related projects. Please see the Optimystics.io/projects-and-funding for details on our funding and related projects.", 'website': 'https://optimystics.io'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': '415745', 'ethAddress': '0xd6c09962e907428112069273d5c0dc861e7b1c57'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Optimystics Tools', 'description': 'Optimystics Tools', 'website': 'https://optimystics.io'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 6}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 2}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': 'Enhances Optimism governance by enabling decentralized decision-making and community events. {'id': 1789, 'project': {'name': 'Tribuni Telegram Bot', 'description': "Delegates are the cornerstone of Optimism's governance system. Active and well-informed delegates lead to resilient and sound governance. However, delegates need to process a lot of information, and often find it challenging to stay up-to-date. We are humans after all.\\n\\nTo help delegates stay active and well-informed, my team launched Tribuni - a free telegram mini-app built for delegates. Tribuni sends you quality AI proposal summaries, vote reminders and OP forum activity digest via Telegram. Delegates never miss a vote or an important discussion in OP ecosystem as long as they're on Telegram.\\n\\nAs of Sep 2024, Tribuni supports people managing 28 OP delegate profiles with ~28M vote power combined. Tribuni has become an indispensable part of their delegate workflow. ", 'website': 'https://tribuni.vercel.app/'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': '415745', 'ethAddress': '0xd6c09962e907428112069273d5c0dc861e7b1c57'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Tribuni Telegram Bot', 'description': 'Tribuni Telegram Bot', 'website': 'https://tribuni.vercel.app/'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 8}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 3}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': 'Enhances governance by keeping delegates informed with AI-gen proposal summaries, voting reminders, and forum activity digests, ensuring efficient participation and accessible information on telegram'}]}

{'id': 2030, 'project': {'name': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'description': "We are the team behind the Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard, a comprehensive tool designed to empower the Optimism Collective through transparency and data-driven insights. Our dashboard provides essential governance metrics such as participation rates, voting power distribution, delegates' performance, and voting history. By continuously refining our features based on community feedback, we've enriched stakeholder engagement and informed decision-making processes.

Since last year, we've introduced significant enhancements to the dashboard, including:

Citizen House Integration: We now provide comprehensive data visualization tools for the Citizen House, focusing on Badgeholder analytics and veto proposals. This update enables a clearer understanding of activities within the Citizen House and enhances transparency around proposal results and participation.

RetroPGF Project Analytics: Our dashboard now offers detailed tracking and insights into RetroPGF projects, including an Application Funnel Overview that displays the entire project application process, from submission to decision. We also provide analytics on ongoing and upcoming RetroPGF projects, including RetroPGF 3 & 4, ensuring that the community can better understand and monitor project dynamics and impact.

UI and User Experience Improvements: We revamped the user interface, enhancing the visibility of delegate voting power and improving the navigation bar for easier interaction. Our new delegate card feature allows for more detailed and interactive insights, making it easier for users to track individual delegate activity.

Partial Delegation Integration: We introduced detailed insights into the sources of a delegate's voting power, distinguishing between partial and full delegations. This feature provides a more granular view of each delegate’s influence within the governance process.

Delegate Ranking Bump Chart: A dynamic tool that visualizes the evolution of delegates’ voting power over various timeframes, offering a detailed view of ranking changes to better understand the governance dynamics.

Through these updates, the Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard has continued to foster a culture of accountability, transparency, and informed governance across the Optimism Collective, empowering stakeholders to make astute, data-driven decisions.", 'website': 'https://optimism.curiahub.xyz/'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': 394600, 'ethAddress': '0x8abbbae6cf196701b9d4be696cdd418560e5fca3'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'description': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'website': 'https://optimism.curiahub.xyz/'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 9}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 2}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}]}

{'id': 2012, 'project': {'name': 'Optimism Newsfeed + Assistant', 'description': 'We’re building AI tools for DAOs and Delegates, so they can work better, faster.

{'id': 1881, 'project': {'name': 'Gravity DAO', 'description': 'GravityDAO is an organization that develops conflict management, trust creation, and leadership as public goods. We are pioneers in promoting governance standards for web3 organizations, like mediation between peers, decentralized enforcement of graduated sanctions, and continued education on human development, strategic planning, and leadership.

We created a free online course about conflict management and trust creation in 5 languages, https://gravitydao.org/online-courses/ and we have trained many communities and individuals to transform conflict into fuel for growth. Right now we are developing content for a second free online course, focussed on the topic of leadership and strategy for Web3 projects, and we hope to publish it in the first months of 2025. 

Gravity was founded in 2021, and we have been building a reputation thanks to the years and the communities we have impacted positively with our frameworks, such as Optimism. 

We aspire to be supported in this retro funding 6 because we are working on the cutting-edge of sociotechnical systems design. {'id': 2030, 'project': {'name': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'description': "We are the team behind the Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard, a comprehensive tool designed to empower the Optimism Collective through transparency and data-driven insights. Our dashboard provides essential governance metrics such as participation rates, voting power distribution, delegates' performance, and voting history. By continuously refining our features based on community feedback, we've enriched stakeholder engagement and informed decision-making processes.

Since last year, we've introduced significant enhancements to the dashboard, including:

Citizen House Integration: We now provide comprehensive data visualization tools for the Citizen House, focusing on Badgeholder analytics and veto proposals. This update enables a clearer understanding of activities within the Citizen House and enhances transparency around proposal results and participation.

RetroPGF Project Analytics: Our dashboard now offers detailed tracking and insights into RetroPGF projects, including an Application Funnel Overview that displays the entire project application process, from submission to decision. We also provide analytics on ongoing and upcoming RetroPGF projects, including RetroPGF 3 & 4, ensuring that the community can better understand and monitor project dynamics and impact.

UI and User Experience Improvements: We revamped the user interface, enhancing the visibility of delegate voting power and improving the navigation bar for easier interaction. Our new delegate card feature allows for more detailed and interactive insights, making it easier for users to track individual delegate activity.

Partial Delegation Integration: We introduced detailed insights into the sources of a delegate's voting power, distinguishing between partial and full delegations. This feature provides a more granular view of each delegate’s influence within the governance process.

Delegate Ranking Bump Chart: A dynamic tool that visualizes the evolution of delegates’ voting power over various timeframes, offering a detailed view of ranking changes to better understand the governance dynamics.

Through these updates, the Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard has continued to foster a culture of accountability, transparency, and informed governance across the Optimism Collective, empowering stakeholders to make astute, data-driven decisions.", 'website': 'https://optimism.curiahub.xyz/'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': '328679', 'ethAddress': '0xf01dd015bc442d872275a79b9cae84a6ff9b2a27'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'description': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'website': 'https://optimism.curiahub.xyz/'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 10}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 3}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': 'A very great tool for delegate, citizen and voting analytics. {'id': 1865, 'project': {'name': 'Superfluid', 'description': "Superfluid is the leading asset streaming protocol that brings subscriptions, salaries, vesting, and rewards distributions to DAOs and crypto-native businesses worldwide.

The protocol has been live on Optimism since March 2022 and on Base since July 2023. It has been empowering developers with a crypto-native financial primitive, money streaming, and a modular smart contracts framework to build applications that leverage a formula-based balance and gasless, liquid, ongoing value transfer.

To date 31,769 streams have been started on Optimism and 577,985 on Base for a combined total volume of over $170M.

Superfluid is designed to minimize its TVL in favor of making assets available to sender or recipient at all times, minimizing funds locked in smart contracts. As such its impact is better measures in total volume transferred, number of total or active streams, total number of users and daily active users. When measuring the protocol activity it's important to not only rely on the on-chain transaction to smart contracts, but also on the the inner mechanics of the protocol (i.e. by evaluating the actions triggered via callData or by using the protocol subgraph).

On the alignment with Optimism and Retro Funding Round 4
- Superfluid is builder-centric. A developer tool with clear focus on onboarding more developers to build more apps. As such, it’s additive to Optimism’s own goals.
- Superfluid is supporting long term, real world use cases, like Salaries, Subscriptions, Memberships, Rentals, Airdrops, Grants distribution as well as entirely novel applications in DeFi, SocialFi and beyond.

Superfluid Protocol has been used by the Optimism Foundation to stream the RPGF3 grants, and will be used again in the upcoming RPGF4 round, providing the rails for a seamless funds distribution.

The protocol has been designed around builders and developers, with a set of tools available for building, debugging and data retrieval that empower new applications development. Here you can see an overview of projects built on Superfluid that have added value (and usage) to the Optimism and Base networks: https://www.superfluid.finance/post/how-superfluid-protocol-is-empowering-onchain-builders

If you have any questions or would like to learn more about Superfluid, please reach out to mdali.eth on Warpcast or Twitter/X.", 'website': ''}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': '193400', 'ethAddress': '0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Superfluid', 'description': 'Superfluid', 'website': ''}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 8}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 3}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': 'Very great experience of grant distribution'}]}

{'id': 1865, 'project': {'name': 'Superfluid', 'description': "Superfluid is the leading asset streaming protocol that brings subscriptions, salaries, vesting, and rewards distributions to DAOs and crypto-native businesses worldwide.

The protocol has been live on Optimism since March 2022 and on Base since July 2023. It has been empowering developers with a crypto-native financial primitive, money streaming, and a modular smart contracts framework to build applications that leverage a formula-based balance and gasless, liquid, ongoing value transfer.

To date 31,769 streams have been started on Optimism and 577,985 on Base for a combined total volume of over $170M.

Superfluid is designed to minimize its TVL in favor of making assets available to sender or recipient at all times, minimizing funds locked in smart contracts. As such its impact is better measures in total volume transferred, number of total or active streams, total number of users and daily active users. When measuring the protocol activity it's important to not only rely on the on-chain transaction to smart contracts, but also on the the inner mechanics of the protocol (i.e. by evaluating the actions triggered via callData or by using the protocol subgraph).

On the alignment with Optimism and Retro Funding Round 4
- Superfluid is builder-centric. A developer tool with clear focus on onboarding more developers to build more apps. As such, it’s additive to Optimism’s own goals.
- Superfluid is supporting long term, real world use cases, like Salaries, Subscriptions, Memberships, Rentals, Airdrops, Grants distribution as well as entirely novel applications in DeFi, SocialFi and beyond.

Superfluid Protocol has been used by the Optimism Foundation to stream the RPGF3 grants, and will be used again in the upcoming RPGF4 round, providing the rails for a seamless funds distribution.

The protocol has been designed around builders and developers, with a set of tools available for building, debugging and data retrieval that empower new applications development. {'id': 2030, 'project': {'name': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'description': "We are the team behind the Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard, a comprehensive tool designed to empower the Optimism Collective through transparency and data-driven insights. Our dashboard provides essential governance metrics such as participation rates, voting power distribution, delegates' performance, and voting history. By continuously refining our features based on community feedback, we've enriched stakeholder engagement and informed decision-making processes.

Since last year, we've introduced significant enhancements to the dashboard, including:

Citizen House Integration: We now provide comprehensive data visualization tools for the Citizen House, focusing on Badgeholder analytics and veto proposals. This update enables a clearer understanding of activities within the Citizen House and enhances transparency around proposal results and participation.

RetroPGF Project Analytics: Our dashboard now offers detailed tracking and insights into RetroPGF projects, including an Application Funnel Overview that displays the entire project application process, from submission to decision. We also provide analytics on ongoing and upcoming RetroPGF projects, including RetroPGF 3 & 4, ensuring that the community can better understand and monitor project dynamics and impact.

UI and User Experience Improvements: We revamped the user interface, enhancing the visibility of delegate voting power and improving the navigation bar for easier interaction. Our new delegate card feature allows for more detailed and interactive insights, making it easier for users to track individual delegate activity.

Partial Delegation Integration: We introduced detailed insights into the sources of a delegate's voting power, distinguishing between partial and full delegations. This feature provides a more granular view of each delegate’s influence within the governance process.

Delegate Ranking Bump Chart: A dynamic tool that visualizes the evolution of delegates’ voting power over various timeframes, offering a detailed view of ranking changes to better understand the governance dynamics.

Through these updates, the Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard has continued to foster a culture of accountability, transparency, and informed governance across the Optimism Collective, empowering stakeholders to make astute, data-driven decisions.", 'website': 'https://optimism.curiahub.xyz/'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': 777864, 'ethAddress': '0x64fed9e56b548343e7bb47c49ecd7ffa9f1a34fe'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'description': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'website': 'https://optimism.curiahub.xyz/'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 9}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 2}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}]}

{'id': 2117, 'project': {'name': 'Onchain Impact Metrics for Retro Funding', 'description': 'Open Source Observer is a public good that helps communities measure impact and improve grant effectiveness. During Retro Funding 4 (Onchain Builders), we collaborated closely with the Citizens House to develop a comprehensive suite of onchain impact metrics and power the first "metrics-based voting" experiment.

We created a first-of-its-kind data pipeline for the Superchain: not only the data but also all source code, query logic, and underlying infrastructure is publicly available for use. With data generously provided by Goldsky, we built a unified Superchain event model covering all OP Stack chains (OP Mainnet, Base, Fraxtal, Metal, Mode, and Zora). We wrote custom logic for discovering contract deployments and attributing them to specific projects per RF4 requirements. With our friends at OpenRank, Passport, and the OP Labs data team, we designed a "trusted user model", intended to identify transaction and onchain activity from high reputation users. These models provided the foundation for calculating a range of quantitative indicators to assess the contributions of onchain builders across these chains. All methodologies, data sources, and analysis tools used in developing these metrics are publicly available.

We also maintain an important community resource called OSS Directory: a public repository of Optimism projects and their associated GitHub repos, NPM packages, deployers, contracts, and other open source artifacts, with a strict schema and validation logic to ensure consistency. There are more than 500 Optimism projects in the directory, with new submissions and updates coming in every week. During the RF4 sign-up period, we received 50+ new submissions and made numerous updates to existing projects. 

The journey to arrive at a final set of onchain impact metrics was iterative and collaborative. We worked closely with the Foundation and badgeholders to discover and refine the metrics through workshops, surveys, and asynchronous feedabck. This collaboration not only provided valuable insights for Retro Funding 4 but also laid the groundwork for more sophisticated impact assessment in subsequent rounds.

In all the work leading up to the final voting, we maintained our commitment to openness and reproducibility, and wrote extensively about the process to arrive at the final set of metrics on our blog and the Optimism governance forum.', 'website': 'https://www.opensource.observer'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': 4469, 'ethAddress': '0x8dd75bcf926df8f50be9bd6532628e9b071bd2c9'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Onchain Impact Metrics for Retro Funding', 'description': 'Onchain Impact Metrics for Retro Funding', 'website': 'https://www.opensource.observer'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 10}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 3}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}]}

{'id': 1865, 'project': {'name': 'Superfluid', 'description': "Superfluid is the leading asset streaming protocol that brings subscriptions, salaries, vesting, and rewards distributions to DAOs and crypto-native businesses worldwide.

The protocol has been live on Optimism since March 2022 and on Base since July 2023. It has been empowering developers with a crypto-native financial primitive, money streaming, and a modular smart contracts framework to build applications that leverage a formula-based balance and gasless, liquid, ongoing value transfer.

To date 31,769 streams have been started on Optimism and 577,985 on Base for a combined total volume of over $170M.

Superfluid is designed to minimize its TVL in favor of making assets available to sender or recipient at all times, minimizing funds locked in smart contracts. As such its impact is better measures in total volume transferred, number of total or active streams, total number of users and daily active users. When measuring the protocol activity it's important to not only rely on the on-chain transaction to smart contracts, but also on the the inner mechanics of the protocol (i.e. by evaluating the actions triggered via callData or by using the protocol subgraph).

On the alignment with Optimism and Retro Funding Round 4
- Superfluid is builder-centric. A developer tool with clear focus on onboarding more developers to build more apps. As such, it’s additive to Optimism’s own goals.
- Superfluid is supporting long term, real world use cases, like Salaries, Subscriptions, Memberships, Rentals, Airdrops, Grants distribution as well as entirely novel applications in DeFi, SocialFi and beyond.

Superfluid Protocol has been used by the Optimism Foundation to stream the RPGF3 grants, and will be used again in the upcoming RPGF4 round, providing the rails for a seamless funds distribution.

The protocol has been designed around builders and developers, with a set of tools available for building, debugging and data retrieval that empower new applications development. Here you can see an overview of projects built on Superfluid that have added value (and usage) to the Optimism and Base networks: https://www.superfluid.finance/post/how-superfluid-protocol-is-empowering-onchain-builders

If you have any questions or would like to learn more about Superfluid, please reach out to mdali.eth on Warpcast or Twitter/X.", 'website': ''}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': 4469, 'ethAddress': '0x8dd75bcf926df8f50be9bd6532628e9b071bd2c9'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Superfluid', 'description': 'Superfluid', 'website': ''}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 10}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 3}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}]}

{'id': 1789, 'project': {'name': 'Tribuni Telegram Bot', 'description': "Delegates are the cornerstone of Optimism's governance system. Active and well-informed delegates lead to resilient and sound governance. However, delegates need to process a lot of information, and often find it challenging to stay up-to-date. We are humans after all.\\n\\nTo help delegates stay active and well-informed, my team launched Tribuni - a free telegram mini-app built for delegates. Tribuni sends you quality AI proposal summaries, vote reminders and OP forum activity digest via Telegram. {'id': 2030, 'project': {'name': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'description': "We are the team behind the Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard, a comprehensive tool designed to empower the Optimism Collective through transparency and data-driven insights. Our dashboard provides essential governance metrics such as participation rates, voting power distribution, delegates' performance, and voting history. By continuously refining our features based on community feedback, we've enriched stakeholder engagement and informed decision-making processes.

Since last year, we've introduced significant enhancements to the dashboard, including:

Citizen House Integration: We now provide comprehensive data visualization tools for the Citizen House, focusing on Badgeholder analytics and veto proposals. This update enables a clearer understanding of activities within the Citizen House and enhances transparency around proposal results and participation.

RetroPGF Project Analytics: Our dashboard now offers detailed tracking and insights into RetroPGF projects, including an Application Funnel Overview that displays the entire project application process, from submission to decision. We also provide analytics on ongoing and upcoming RetroPGF projects, including RetroPGF 3 & 4, ensuring that the community can better understand and monitor project dynamics and impact.

UI and User Experience Improvements: We revamped the user interface, enhancing the visibility of delegate voting power and improving the navigation bar for easier interaction. Our new delegate card feature allows for more detailed and interactive insights, making it easier for users to track individual delegate activity.

Partial Delegation Integration: We introduced detailed insights into the sources of a delegate's voting power, distinguishing between partial and full delegations. This feature provides a more granular view of each delegate’s influence within the governance process.

Delegate Ranking Bump Chart: A dynamic tool that visualizes the evolution of delegates’ voting power over various timeframes, offering a detailed view of ranking changes to better understand the governance dynamics.

Through these updates, the Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard has continued to foster a culture of accountability, transparency, and informed governance across the Optimism Collective, empowering stakeholders to make astute, data-driven decisions.", 'website': 'https://optimism.curiahub.xyz/'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': '18391', 'ethAddress': '0x7fc80fad32ec41fd5cfcc14eee9c31953b6b4a8b'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'description': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'website': 'https://optimism.curiahub.xyz/'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 10}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 3}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': 'I use Curia frequently because it includes advanced delegation information and its graphs are very user-friendly. {'id': 2183, 'project': {'name': 'Praise', 'description': 'Praise is an open-source reputation and rewards system designed to recognize, track, and verify community contributions across decentralized ecosystems. By offering simple tools that integrate with both Discord and Farcaster, Praise empowers communities to mint on-chain attestations and cultivate identity and reputation.\nThrough peer recognition on platforms Discord and more recently Farcaster, Praise enables users to acknowledge contributions, whether large or small, and reward them with verifiable on-chain attestations. {'id': 1828, 'project': {'name': 'Pairwise', 'description': 'Pairwise was designed to make voting to distribute Retro Funding simple and fun. Pairwise is an open-source, off-chain voting dapp (like Snapshot) that streamlines community signaling by letting users select between just two options and then aggregating their choices into a quantifiable result.
Pairwise is designed to be user-friendly and intuitive, allowing users to make many simple choices and then the algorithm behind the scenes pumps out a final ranking for them to adjust or approve. 

* RF3: Served as an alternative tool for creating lists and subcategories of 600+ projects.
* RF4: Ran its own independent experiment involving all stakeholders to signal how to distribute RF promoting project discovery with pseudonymous voting.
* RF5: After great work on RF4, was invited to be a fun voting option to gamify and simplify the badgeholder decision making process. Allowing Badgeholders to create their ballot by comparing projects.', 'website': 'https://www.pairwise.vote/'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': 195722, 'ethAddress': '0xe422d6c46a69e989ba6468ccd0435cb0c5c243e3'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Pairwise', 'description': 'Pairwise', 'website': 'https://www.pairwise.vote/'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 5}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 2}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': "I would use Pairwise more if I could do so ofline, just for myself. {'id': 2030, 'project': {'name': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'description': "We are the team behind the Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard, a comprehensive tool designed to empower the Optimism Collective through transparency and data-driven insights. Our dashboard provides essential governance metrics such as participation rates, voting power distribution, delegates' performance, and voting history. By continuously refining our features based on community feedback, we've enriched stakeholder engagement and informed decision-making processes.

Since last year, we've introduced significant enhancements to the dashboard, including:

Citizen House Integration: We now provide comprehensive data visualization tools for the Citizen House, focusing on Badgeholder analytics and veto proposals. This update enables a clearer understanding of activities within the Citizen House and enhances transparency around proposal results and participation.

RetroPGF Project Analytics: Our dashboard now offers detailed tracking and insights into RetroPGF projects, including an Application Funnel Overview that displays the entire project application process, from submission to decision. We also provide analytics on ongoing and upcoming RetroPGF projects, including RetroPGF 3 & 4, ensuring that the community can better understand and monitor project dynamics and impact.

UI and User Experience Improvements: We revamped the user interface, enhancing the visibility of delegate voting power and improving the navigation bar for easier interaction. Our new delegate card feature allows for more detailed and interactive insights, making it easier for users to track individual delegate activity.

Partial Delegation Integration: We introduced detailed insights into the sources of a delegate's voting power, distinguishing between partial and full delegations. This feature provides a more granular view of each delegate’s influence within the governance process.

Delegate Ranking Bump Chart: A dynamic tool that visualizes the evolution of delegates’ voting power over various timeframes, offering a detailed view of ranking changes to better understand the governance dynamics.

Through these updates, the Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard has continued to foster a culture of accountability, transparency, and informed governance across the Optimism Collective, empowering stakeholders to make astute, data-driven decisions.", 'website': 'https://optimism.curiahub.xyz/'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': '384391', 'ethAddress': '0xad4f365a550835d40dc2e95fdffa1e4edd3fbe14'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'description': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'website': 'https://optimism.curiahub.xyz/'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 9}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 1}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}]}

{'id': 1986, 'project': {'name': 'DeVouch powered by Giveth', 'description': 'Giveth is an open-source, radically transparent, user-friendly donation platform that supports verified public goods projects to raise crypto with zero added fees and no intermediaries. Today, Giveth supports donations on  Optimism, Ethereum Mainnet, Base, Celo, as well as 7 other chains, and several OP Governance projects, such as growthepie, DAOstar, Pairwise & EAS raise funds on our platform.

Recently, in coordination with the Optimism Token House, we launched DeVouch, a system for members of reputable organizations in the Ethereum ecosystem to vouch for projects looking to raise funding. It was created with special attention to the Optimism Retro Funding mechanism.

How does it work?

By vouching for a project, the organization can lend its credibility to the project, building confidence for those looking to support it with funding.

DeVouch collects projects from Gitcoin, Giveth, and Optimism Retro Funding rounds and showcases them in a single place, allowing all users to either vouch for or flag each project. Visitors to the website can see the vouches and flags received by each project, which were tracked by the "Attester Group" that the vouch or flag came from. 

Attester Groups are formed by looking at on-chain Attestation Data from EAS on Optimism to know who belongs to which organization or community sub-set by which Attestations have been issued to them and by whom. An example of Attester Groups are RetroFunding 5 voters or Gitcoin passport holders.

This allows members of these groups to lend their reputation to the project looking for funding. However, attesting with DeVouch is a double-edged sword, if a project seems suspicious or untrustworthy then they could also receive a flag, warning others to think twice before supporting this project.

DeVouch is open-source and allows any platform or individual to query DeVouch data using our graphQL API as well as contribute by the issuance of attestations using the DeVouch schema. Anyone can also add their Attester Group to DeVouch by making a simple PR on the DeVouch Github Repository

Who uses it?

DeVouch was launched in early June 2024, and has been featured as additional tooling in Retro Funding 5. Giveth is also integrating it to provide Decentralized Verification of projects seeking funding on the platform.

Considering that we launched on June 12th of this year, the over 700 onchain attestations that’ve happened through DeVouch shows that there are good expectations, regarding the growth of users.

Also, to map potential, we look at the demand for such a service, and specifically with Optimism, we have over 591 projects (according to Alchemy) between dApps, dexes, etc., which are all looking to take fundraising opportunities and a piece of the $3.3B in Public Goods funding that was set aside by the Optimism Collective. 

A decentralized vouching system is essential to bringing more efficiency to allocating funds, as well as to map the reputation of each project by the entire Optimism Community. Is a project a scam? Flag it! Is a project legit? Vouch for it!
', 'website': 'https://devouch.xyz/'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': '384391', 'ethAddress': '0xad4f365a550835d40dc2e95fdffa1e4edd3fbe14'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'DeVouch powered by Giveth', 'description': 'DeVouch powered by Giveth', 'website': 'https://devouch.xyz/'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 9}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 3}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}]}

{'id': 1881, 'project': {'name': 'Gravity DAO', 'description': 'GravityDAO is an organization that develops conflict management, trust creation, and leadership as public goods. We are pioneers in promoting governance standards for web3 organizations, like mediation between peers, decentralized enforcement of graduated sanctions, and continued education on human development, strategic planning, and leadership.

We created a free online course about conflict management and trust creation in 5 languages, https://gravitydao.org/online-courses/ and we have trained many communities and individuals to transform conflict into fuel for growth. Right now we are developing content for a second free online course, focussed on the topic of leadership and strategy for Web3 projects, and we hope to publish it in the first months of 2025. 

Gravity was founded in 2021, and we have been building a reputation thanks to the years and the communities we have impacted positively with our frameworks, such as Optimism. 

We aspire to be supported in this retro funding 6 because we are working on the cutting-edge of sociotechnical systems design. The problems we tackle are the most common and shared for any project and community, so the solutions we bring are evergreen and have a wide range of impact.', 'website': 'https://gravitydao.org/'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': '384391', 'ethAddress': '0xad4f365a550835d40dc2e95fdffa1e4edd3fbe14'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Gravity DAO', 'description': 'Gravity DAO', 'website': 'https://gravitydao.org/'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 10}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 3}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': "Tools that support delegates' and citizens' insights into governance performance and history"}]}

{'id': 1865, 'project': {'name': 'Superfluid', 'description': "Superfluid is the leading asset streaming protocol that brings subscriptions, salaries, vesting, and rewards distributions to DAOs and crypto-native businesses worldwide.

The protocol has been live on Optimism since March 2022 and on Base since July 2023. It has been empowering developers with a crypto-native financial primitive, money streaming, and a modular smart contracts framework to build applications that leverage a formula-based balance and gasless, liquid, ongoing value transfer.

To date 31,769 streams have been started on Optimism and 577,985 on Base for a combined total volume of over $170M.

Superfluid is designed to minimize its TVL in favor of making assets available to sender or recipient at all times, minimizing funds locked in smart contracts. As such its impact is better measures in total volume transferred, number of total or active streams, total number of users and daily active users. When measuring the protocol activity it's important to not only rely on the on-chain transaction to smart contracts, but also on the the inner mechanics of the protocol (i.e. by evaluating the actions triggered via callData or by using the protocol subgraph).

On the alignment with Optimism and Retro Funding Round 4
- Superfluid is builder-centric. A developer tool with clear focus on onboarding more developers to build more apps. As such, it’s additive to Optimism’s own goals.
- Superfluid is supporting long term, real world use cases, like Salaries, Subscriptions, Memberships, Rentals, Airdrops, Grants distribution as well as entirely novel applications in DeFi, SocialFi and beyond.

Superfluid Protocol has been used by the Optimism Foundation to stream the RPGF3 grants, and will be used again in the upcoming RPGF4 round, providing the rails for a seamless funds distribution.

The protocol has been designed around builders and developers, with a set of tools available for building, debugging and data retrieval that empower new applications development. Here you can see an overview of projects built on Superfluid that have added value (and usage) to the Optimism and Base networks: https://www.superfluid.finance/post/how-superfluid-protocol-is-empowering-onchain-builders

If you have any questions or would like to learn more about Superfluid, please reach out to mdali.eth on Warpcast or Twitter/X.", 'website': ''}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': 318387, 'ethAddress': '0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Superfluid', 'description': 'Superfluid', 'website': ''}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 10}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 3}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}]}

Pairwise is an open-source, off-chain voting dapp (like Snapshot) that streamlines community signaling by letting users select between just two options and then aggregating their choices into a quantifiable result.

* RF5: After great work on RF4, was invited to be a fun voting option to gamify and simplify the badgeholder decision making process. {'id': 2117, 'project': {'name': 'Onchain Impact Metrics for Retro Funding', 'description': 'Open Source Observer is a public good that helps communities measure impact and improve grant effectiveness. During Retro Funding 4 (Onchain Builders), we collaborated closely with the Citizens House to develop a comprehensive suite of onchain impact metrics and power the first "metrics-based voting" experiment.

We created a first-of-its-kind data pipeline for the Superchain: not only the data but also all source code, query logic, and underlying infrastructure is publicly available for use. With data generously provided by Goldsky, we built a unified Superchain event model covering all OP Stack chains (OP Mainnet, Base, Fraxtal, Metal, Mode, and Zora). We wrote custom logic for discovering contract deployments and attributing them to specific projects per RF4 requirements. With our friends at OpenRank, Passport, and the OP Labs data team, we designed a "trusted user model", intended to identify transaction and onchain activity from high reputation users. These models provided the foundation for calculating a range of quantitative indicators to assess the contributions of onchain builders across these chains. All methodologies, data sources, and analysis tools used in developing these metrics are publicly available.

We also maintain an important community resource called OSS Directory: a public repository of Optimism projects and their associated GitHub repos, NPM packages, deployers, contracts, and other open source artifacts, with a strict schema and validation logic to ensure consistency. There are more than 500 Optimism projects in the directory, with new submissions and updates coming in every week. During the RF4 sign-up period, we received 50+ new submissions and made numerous updates to existing projects. 

The journey to arrive at a final set of onchain impact metrics was iterative and collaborative. We worked closely with the Foundation and badgeholders to discover and refine the metrics through workshops, surveys, and asynchronous feedabck. This collaboration not only provided valuable insights for Retro Funding 4 but also laid the groundwork for more sophisticated impact assessment in subsequent rounds.

In all the work leading up to the final voting, we maintained our commitment to openness and reproducibility, and wrote extensively about the process to arrive at the final set of metrics on our blog and the Optimism governance forum.', 'website': 'https://www.opensource.observer'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': 318387, 'ethAddress': '0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Onchain Impact Metrics for Retro Funding', 'description': 'Onchain Impact Metrics for Retro Funding', 'website': 'https://www.opensource.observer'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 9}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 3}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}]}

{'id': 1881, 'project': {'name': 'Gravity DAO', 'description': 'GravityDAO is an organization that develops conflict management, trust creation, and leadership as public goods. We are pioneers in promoting governance standards for web3 organizations, like mediation between peers, decentralized enforcement of graduated sanctions, and continued education on human development, strategic planning, and leadership.

We created a free online course about conflict management and trust creation in 5 languages, https://gravitydao.org/online-courses/ and we have trained many communities and individuals to transform conflict into fuel for growth. Right now we are developing content for a second free online course, focussed on the topic of leadership and strategy for Web3 projects, and we hope to publish it in the first months of 2025. 

Gravity was founded in 2021, and we have been building a reputation thanks to the years and the communities we have impacted positively with our frameworks, such as Optimism. 

We aspire to be supported in this retro funding 6 because we are working on the cutting-edge of sociotechnical systems design. The problems we tackle are the most common and shared for any project and community, so the solutions we bring are evergreen and have a wide range of impact.', 'website': 'https://gravitydao.org/'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': 318387, 'ethAddress': '0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Gravity DAO', 'description': 'Gravity DAO', 'website': 'https://gravitydao.org/'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 8}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 2}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}]}

Our initial toolset laid the groundwork for fractal democracy experiments, enabling peer-reviewed contribution evaluation and democratic council formation. This has evolved into a comprehensive ecosystem of governance tools, including a comprehensive Respect Games app for gamified governance, Fractalgram app for live community engagement, and ORDAO smart contracts for optimistic, respect-based onchain execution. By providing this infrastructure, we've created a laboratory for governance innovation within the Optimism ecosystem. Our tools have not only supported Optimism Fractal but have also been adopted by other communities, demonstrating their versatility and potential for wider impact in decentralized governance.

This work has not been funded by the Collective outside of the RetroPGF Round 3 grant shown below, which supported the team who started Optimism Fractal as well as our work with several other related projects. {'id': 1865, 'project': {'name': 'Superfluid', 'description': "Superfluid is the leading asset streaming protocol that brings subscriptions, salaries, vesting, and rewards distributions to DAOs and crypto-native businesses worldwide.

The protocol has been live on Optimism since March 2022 and on Base since July 2023. It has been empowering developers with a crypto-native financial primitive, money streaming, and a modular smart contracts framework to build applications that leverage a formula-based balance and gasless, liquid, ongoing value transfer.

To date 31,769 streams have been started on Optimism and 577,985 on Base for a combined total volume of over $170M.

Superfluid is designed to minimize its TVL in favor of making assets available to sender or recipient at all times, minimizing funds locked in smart contracts. As such its impact is better measures in total volume transferred, number of total or active streams, total number of users and daily active users. When measuring the protocol activity it's important to not only rely on the on-chain transaction to smart contracts, but also on the the inner mechanics of the protocol (i.e. by evaluating the actions triggered via callData or by using the protocol subgraph).

On the alignment with Optimism and Retro Funding Round 4
- Superfluid is builder-centric. A developer tool with clear focus on onboarding more developers to build more apps. As such, it’s additive to Optimism’s own goals.
- Superfluid is supporting long term, real world use cases, like Salaries, Subscriptions, Memberships, Rentals, Airdrops, Grants distribution as well as entirely novel applications in DeFi, SocialFi and beyond.

Superfluid Protocol has been used by the Optimism Foundation to stream the RPGF3 grants, and will be used again in the upcoming RPGF4 round, providing the rails for a seamless funds distribution.

The protocol has been designed around builders and developers, with a set of tools available for building, debugging and data retrieval that empower new applications development. Here you can see an overview of projects built on Superfluid that have added value (and usage) to the Optimism and Base networks: https://www.superfluid.finance/post/how-superfluid-protocol-is-empowering-onchain-builders

If you have any questions or would like to learn more about Superfluid, please reach out to mdali.eth on Warpcast or Twitter/X.", 'website': ''}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': 19412, 'ethAddress': '0x5a5d9ab7b1bd978f80909503ebb828879daca9c3'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Superfluid', 'description': 'Superfluid', 'website': ''}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 10}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 2}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': 'As a grant recipient, Superfluid is awesome. {'id': 1828, 'project': {'name': 'Pairwise', 'description': 'Pairwise was designed to make voting to distribute Retro Funding simple and fun. Pairwise is an open-source, off-chain voting dapp (like Snapshot) that streamlines community signaling by letting users select between just two options and then aggregating their choices into a quantifiable result.
Pairwise is designed to be user-friendly and intuitive, allowing users to make many simple choices and then the algorithm behind the scenes pumps out a final ranking for them to adjust or approve. 

* RF3: Served as an alternative tool for creating lists and subcategories of 600+ projects.
* RF4: Ran its own independent experiment involving all stakeholders to signal how to distribute RF promoting project discovery with pseudonymous voting.
* RF5: After great work on RF4, was invited to be a fun voting option to gamify and simplify the badgeholder decision making process. {'id': 1865, 'project': {'name': 'Superfluid', 'description': "Superfluid is the leading asset streaming protocol that brings subscriptions, salaries, vesting, and rewards distributions to DAOs and crypto-native businesses worldwide.

The protocol has been live on Optimism since March 2022 and on Base since July 2023. It has been empowering developers with a crypto-native financial primitive, money streaming, and a modular smart contracts framework to build applications that leverage a formula-based balance and gasless, liquid, ongoing value transfer.

To date 31,769 streams have been started on Optimism and 577,985 on Base for a combined total volume of over $170M.

Superfluid is designed to minimize its TVL in favor of making assets available to sender or recipient at all times, minimizing funds locked in smart contracts. As such its impact is better measures in total volume transferred, number of total or active streams, total number of users and daily active users. When measuring the protocol activity it's important to not only rely on the on-chain transaction to smart contracts, but also on the the inner mechanics of the protocol (i.e. by evaluating the actions triggered via callData or by using the protocol subgraph).

On the alignment with Optimism and Retro Funding Round 4
- Superfluid is builder-centric. A developer tool with clear focus on onboarding more developers to build more apps. As such, it’s additive to Optimism’s own goals.
- Superfluid is supporting long term, real world use cases, like Salaries, Subscriptions, Memberships, Rentals, Airdrops, Grants distribution as well as entirely novel applications in DeFi, SocialFi and beyond.

Superfluid Protocol has been used by the Optimism Foundation to stream the RPGF3 grants, and will be used again in the upcoming RPGF4 round, providing the rails for a seamless funds distribution.

The protocol has been designed around builders and developers, with a set of tools available for building, debugging and data retrieval that empower new applications development. Here you can see an overview of projects built on Superfluid that have added value (and usage) to the Optimism and Base networks: https://www.superfluid.finance/post/how-superfluid-protocol-is-empowering-onchain-builders

If you have any questions or would like to learn more about Superfluid, please reach out to mdali.eth on Warpcast or Twitter/X.", 'website': ''}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': 18344, 'ethAddress': '0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Superfluid', 'description': 'Superfluid', 'website': ''}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 8}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 2}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': 'The token distribution through Superfluid was excellent and easy to use.'}]}

{'id': 2030, 'project': {'name': 'Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard', 'description': "We are the team behind the Curia OP Governance Analytics Dashboard, a comprehensive tool designed to empower the Optimism Collective through transparency and data-driven insights. Our dashboard provides essential governance metrics such as participation rates, voting power distribution, delegates' performance, and voting history. By continuously refining our features based on community feedback, we've enriched stakeholder engagement and informed decision-making processes.

Since last year, we've introduced significant enhancements to the dashboard, including:

Citizen House Integration: We now provide comprehensive data visualization tools for the Citizen House, focusing on Badgeholder analytics and veto proposals. This update enables a clearer understanding of activities within the Citizen House and enhances transparency around proposal results and participation.

RetroPGF Project Analytics: Our dashboard now offers detailed tracking and insights into RetroPGF projects, including an Application Funnel Overview that displays the entire project application process, from submission to decision. We also provide analytics on ongoing and upcoming RetroPGF projects, including RetroPGF 3 & 4, ensuring that the community can better understand and monitor project dynamics and impact.

UI and User Experience Improvements: We revamped the user interface, enhancing the visibility of delegate voting power and improving the navigation bar for easier interaction. Our new delegate card feature allows for more detailed and interactive insights, making it easier for users to track individual delegate activity.

Partial Delegation Integration: We introduced detailed insights into the sources of a delegate's voting power, distinguishing between partial and full delegations. This feature provides a more granular view of each delegate’s influence within the governance process.

Delegate Ranking Bump Chart: A dynamic tool that visualizes the evolution of delegates’ voting power over various timeframes, offering a detailed view of ranking changes to better understand the governance dynamics.

{'id': 1865, 'project': {'name': 'Superfluid', 'description': "Superfluid is the leading asset streaming protocol that brings subscriptions, salaries, vesting, and rewards distributions to DAOs and crypto-native businesses worldwide.

The protocol has been live on Optimism since March 2022 and on Base since July 2023. It has been empowering developers with a crypto-native financial primitive, money streaming, and a modular smart contracts framework to build applications that leverage a formula-based balance and gasless, liquid, ongoing value transfer.

To date 31,769 streams have been started on Optimism and 577,985 on Base for a combined total volume of over $170M.

Superfluid is designed to minimize its TVL in favor of making assets available to sender or recipient at all times, minimizing funds locked in smart contracts. As such its impact is better measures in total volume transferred, number of total or active streams, total number of users and daily active users. When measuring the protocol activity it's important to not only rely on the on-chain transaction to smart contracts, but also on the the inner mechanics of the protocol (i.e. by evaluating the actions triggered via callData or by using the protocol subgraph).

On the alignment with Optimism and Retro Funding Round 4
- Superfluid is builder-centric. A developer tool with clear focus on onboarding more developers to build more apps. As such, it’s additive to Optimism’s own goals.
- Superfluid is supporting long term, real world use cases, like Salaries, Subscriptions, Memberships, Rentals, Airdrops, Grants distribution as well as entirely novel applications in DeFi, SocialFi and beyond.

Superfluid Protocol has been used by the Optimism Foundation to stream the RPGF3 grants, and will be used again in the upcoming RPGF4 round, providing the rails for a seamless funds distribution.

The protocol has been designed around builders and developers, with a set of tools available for building, debugging and data retrieval that empower new applications development. Here you can see an overview of projects built on Superfluid that have added value (and usage) to the Optimism and Base networks: https://www.superfluid.finance/post/how-superfluid-protocol-is-empowering-onchain-builders

If you have any questions or would like to learn more about Superfluid, please reach out to mdali.eth on Warpcast or Twitter/X.", 'website': ''}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': '191212', 'ethAddress': '0x4a6894dd556fab996f8d50b521f900caeedc168e'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Superfluid', 'description': 'Superfluid', 'website': ''}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 8}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 2}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': 'The team has been super supportive in helping us stream Retro Funding! {'id': 2011, 'project': {'name': 'Snapshot', 'description': "Snapshot started as a voting platform designed to allow onchain organizations to vote easily without gas fees. Its strength lies in its flexibility and high customization, catering to the diverse needs of its users. This includes options for calculating users' voting power, selecting different voting mechanisms, and managing proposal and vote validation rules.\n\nAs the gas cost dropped with the maturity of L2s and the need for more decentralized and trustless voting grew, we developed Snapshot X, an onchain voting protocol. Unlike the original Snapshot, Snapshot X operates fully onchain using a set of modular smart contracts. This shift makes Snapshot censorship resistant, with onchain and cross-chain voting power computation and trustless execution, while keeping gas costs to the minimal extent possible.", 'website': 'https://snapshot.box/#/'}, 'reviewer': {'userFID': '191212', 'ethAddress': '0x4a6894dd556fab996f8d50b521f900caeedc168e'}, 'context': {'ecosystems': [{'name': 'Optimism', 'tags': [{'category': 'Governance', 'subcategory': 'Infra & Tooling', 'round': 'RF6'}]}], 'userInterface': 'Impact Garden'}, 'contributions': [{'name': 'Snapshot', 'description': 'Snapshot', 'website': 'https://snapshot.box/#/'}], 'impactAttestations': [{'name': 'Likely to Recommend', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 6}, {'name': 'Feeling if didnt exist', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': 1}, {'name': 'Governance Knowledge', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Useful for Understanding', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'numeric', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Why Effective for Improvements', 'type': 'string', 'value': ''}, {'name': 'Text Review', 'type': 'string', 'value': 'Useful for CH voting!'}]}
